  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the project is to develop a series of studies with state institutions in order to identify programs policies and challenges in the implementation of international standards in relation to indigenous peoples. The products will be input to the dis
cussion and teaching materials all thanks to research workshops (focus groups) to be held with officials and communities.The studies include: 1) Application of Convention 169 by the Carabineros 2) Study of the Route of addressing violence against women in 
two health centers in primary care Araucania region in the light of the standards of Convention 169 and 3) Application of Convention 169 in the relationship between communities and companies.</narrative>
